==English==
===Etymology===
''[[endo-]]'' "inside" + ''[[-onym]]'' "name"
===Noun===
'''endonym'''

#A name used by a people to refer to themselves or their language, as opposed to a name given to them by other groups. For example, ''[[Deutsche]]n'' is the endonym of a people known in English as ''[[German]]''.
